com.ostrichemulators.semtool.rdf.engine.util

Class EngineUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ostrichemulators.semtool.rdf.engine.util.EngineUtil
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class EngineUtil
extends Object
implements Runnable
    A class to centralize Engine operations. This class is thread-safe, and if started as a thread and used to mount repositories, those repositories can be successfully unmounted later.
    Author:
    ryan

      • mount

        public void mount(String loc,
                  boolean updateRepoList,
                  boolean noDupeEx,
                  User user)
           throws EngineManagementException
        Mounts a repository from its database directory, or its SMSS file. Most callers will want to follow a call to mount with one to addRepositoryToList(com.ostrichemulators.semtool.rdf.engine.api.IEngine)
        Parameters:
        loc - either a database file, or database directory, or URL
        updateRepoList - should the repository list be updated once the repository is loaded?
        noDupeEx - if the given SMSS is already loaded, do nothing instead of throwing the usual DuplicateName exception
        user - the user doing the mounting
        Throws:
        EngineManagementException

      • importInsights

        public void importInsights(IEngine engine,
                           File insightsfile,
                           boolean clearfirst)
                    throws IOException,
                           EngineManagementException
        Adds Insights from the given file to the given engine. This function is always safer than doing it yourself, because this function is guaranteed to run on the same thread that opened the KB in the first place.
        Parameters:
        engine - the engine
        insightsfile - the file with the statements to add (could be a legacy "properties" file). If null, this function will clear all insights from the engine without adding anything
        clearfirst - remove the current insights before adding the new ones?
        Throws:
        IOException
        EngineManagementException

      • importInsights
